A 36-year-old woman, Felicia Richard has been arraigned before Osun State Magistrates’ Court sitting in Osogbo for allegedly assaulting two police officers while on duty. The charge presented to the court by the prosecutor, Mr. Idoko John stated that she committed the offence on February 26, 2020. The charge read, “Felicia Richard on the 26th day of February 2020 at about 1.00 Pm at Dada Estate Police Station in the Osogbo did assault one Inspr. Akanmu Fasilat and Cpl Doubara Douboye while performing their lawful duty and thereby committed an offence contrary to and punishable under section 354 of the criminal code cap 34 Vol. Il Laws of Osun State Nigeria 2002. “She conducted herself in a manner likely to cause a breach of the peace at the police station and thereby committed an offence contrary to and punishable under section 249 (d) of the criminal code cap 34 Vol. II Laws of State, Nigeria 2002.” The defendant pleaded not guilty to the two-count charge preferred against her. Her counsel, Mr. Temitope Ayodele applied for bail for his client. He said, “I want to apply for the bail of my client in the most liberal terms and I am assuring this court that if she’s granted bail, she won’t jump bail. She is a nursing mother.” The Magistrate, Adebola Ajanaku granted bail to the accused person in the sum of N100, 000 with one surety in like sum and adjourned the case to 25th March 2020 for hearing.